{% from "source-toggle.njk" import autoToggle %}
{% from "strategy-toggle.njk" import strategyToggle %}

<h2>Protocol: For Each</h2>
<p>Iterates over a collection (Array, Observable, or Promise) and stamps a template for each item.</p>
<h3>Virtual Implementation</h3>
<p>Uses Custom Comments (e.g. <code>&lt;!-- control:for-each --&gt;</code>) to mark the list boundaries. This behaves like a Repeater without a wrapper element.</p>
<h3>Usage Example</h3>
<p>The author writes the canonical HTML (the comment-directive form); the JSX pane below is <strong>generated from it at build time</strong> by the conversion adapter — the comment markers and inner <code>&lt;template&gt;</code> collapse into the customized built-in <code>&lt;template is="for-each"&gt;</code> (see the <a href="/adapters/jsx-adapter/">JSX Adapter</a> mapping, row 8):</p>
{% set forEachHtml %}
<!-- control:for-each items="users" key="id" -->
  <template>
    <div class="user-row">
      <span data-bind="name"></span>
    </div>
  </template>
<!-- /control:for-each -->
{% endset %}
{{ autoToggle("for-each-usage", forEachHtml) }}

<h3>Rendering strategy — for-each <em>is</em> the declarative-static spelling</h3>
<p>The <code>for-each</code> directive only exists because inert HTML can't iterate — it is an artifact of the
<a href="/projects/webcomponents/#protocol-render-strategy">declarative-static render strategy</a>. Switch the
strategy and it becomes a plain <code>.map()</code> (the vdom pane is generated at build time by the cross-strategy
<code>lift</code> compiler):</p>
{% set forEachStrategy %}
<template is="for-each" items="users" item="user" key="id"><div class="user-row">{{ '{{' }} user.name {{ '}}' }}</div></template>
{% endset %}
{{ strategyToggle("for-each-strategy", renderStrategies, forEachStrategy) }}
